    "title": {
        "rendered": "ScrollLock"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "<p>ScrollLock is a content-free React component for declaratively preventing scroll bleed from modal UI to the page body. This component applies a <code>lockscroll</code> class to the <code>document.documentElement</code> and <code>document.scrollingElement</code> elements to stop the body from scrolling. When it is present, the lock is applied.</p>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<p>Declare scroll locking as part of modal UI.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-jsx\">import { useState } from 'react';\nimport { ScrollLock, Button } from '@wordpress/components';\n\nconst MyScrollLock = () =&gt; {\n    const [ isScrollLocked, setIsScrollLocked ] = useState( false );\n\n    const toggleLock = () =&gt; {\n        setIsScrollLocked( ( locked ) =&gt; ! locked ) );\n    };\n\n    return (\n        &lt;div&gt;\n            &lt;Button variant=\"secondary\" onClick={ toggleLock }&gt;\n                Toggle scroll lock\n            &lt;/Button&gt;\n            { isScrollLocked &amp;&amp; &lt;ScrollLock /&gt; }\n            &lt;p&gt;\n                Scroll locked:\n                &lt;strong&gt;{ isScrollLocked ? 'Yes' : 'No' }&lt;/strong&gt;\n            &lt;/p&gt;\n        &lt;/div&gt;\n    );\n};\n</code></pre>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
